Acting Chinese Ambassador to South Africa Nan Li, is thanking the country for its help to combat COVID-19 in China. China has donated a consignment of Personal Protective Equipment to help health and other frontline workers stop the spread of the disease. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - China has donated a consignment of Personal Protective Equipment to help South Africa's health and other frontline workers curb the spread of the disease. At the handover ceremony, acting Chinese Ambassador to South Africa Nan Li thanked South Africa for its earlier help when China began tackling COVID-19. READ: China ready to assist SA with coronavirus Meanwhile, the number of confirmed positive COVID-19 cases in South Africa now stands at 2,415. There have been no new deaths reported. The number of coronavirus tests concluded to date is 87,022.